Triangle $ABC$ has a right angle at $B$, and contains a point $P$ for which $PA = 10$, $PB = 6$, and $\angle APB = \angle BPC = \angle CPA$. Find $PC$.

[asy]
unitsize(0.2 cm);

pair A, B, C, P;

A = (0,14);
B = (0,0);
C = (21*sqrt(3),0);
P = intersectionpoint(arc(B,6,0,180),arc(C,33,0,180));

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(A--P);
draw(B--P);
draw(C--P);

label("$A$", A, NW);
label("$B$", B, SW);
label("$C$", C, SE);
label("$P$", P, NE);
[/asy]

